                    <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="cart image" class="card-img-top">
                    <p class="card-text font-size-14 py-1">The virus that causes COVID-19 spreads easily among people, and more continues to be discovered over time about how it spreads. Data has shown that it spreads mainly from person to person among those in close contact. The virus spreads by respiratory droplets released when someone with the virus coughs, sneezes, breathes,  or talks. These droplets can be inhaled or land in the mouth, nose or eyes of a person nearby.</p>
